NODE_1_length_267451_cov_420.750746	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	189393	191573	.	-	0	ID=MGA_157;product=circularly permuted type 2 ATP-grasp protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011068744.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_01570;note=WP_011068744.1 circularly permuted type 2 ATP-grasp protein (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:99.9%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:0.0e+00],Domain:cl17448:CP_ATPgrasp_2 Circularly permuted ATP-grasp type 2. An ATP-grasp family that is present both as catalytically active and inactive versions. Contextual analysis suggests that it functions in a distinct peptide synthesis/modification system that additionally contains a transglutaminase%2C an NTN-hydrolase%2C the Alpha-E domain%2C and a transglutaminase fused N-terminal to a circularly permuted COOH-NH2 ligase. The inactive forms are often fused N-terminal to the Alpha-E domain. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:2-448%2C Eval:8.8e-171%2C score:496.5],Domain:cl19824:Alpha-E A predicted alpha-helical domain with a conserved ER motif. An uncharacterized alpha helical domain containing a highly conserved ER motif and typically found as a tandem duplication. Contextual analysis suggests that it functions in a distinct peptide synthesis/modification system comprising of a transglutaminase%2C a peptidase of the NTN-hydrolase superfamily%2C an active and inactive circularly permuted ATP-grasp domains and a transglutaminase fused N-terminal to a circularly permuted COOH-NH2 ligase domain. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:482-640%2C Eval:3.9e-12%2C score:65.1%2C C-term missing],MGA_157
