NODE_3_length_128496_cov_354.562471	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	2386	3729	.	-	0	ID=MGA_391;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_03900;note=WP_011068199.1 MDR family MFS transporter (Bifidobacterium) [pid:94.0%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:65.4%25%2C Eval:1.5e-230%2C partial hit],internal stop codon at [3751:3753](-),TIGR:TIGR00711%3B efflux_EmrB: drug resistance MFS transporter%2C drug:H+ antiporter-2 (14 Spanner) (DHA2) family [Name:TIGR00711%2C Eval:4.5e-32%2C score:109.4%2C bias:11.2],COG:COG0517:CBS CBS domain [Category:T%2C Aligned:296-434%2C Eval:2.9e-14%2C score:66.0],Domain:cl26210:MFS_2 MFS/sugar transport protein. The Glycoside-Pentoside-Hexuronide (GPH):Cation Symporter Family (TC 2.A.2) GPH:cation symporters catalyze uptake of sugars in symport with a monovalent cation (H+ or Na+). Members of this family includes transporters for melibiose%2C lactose%2C raffinose%2C glucuronides%2C pentosides and isoprimeverose. Mutants of two groups of these symporters (the melibiose permeases of enteric bacteria%2C and the lactose permease of Streptococcus thermophilus) have been isolated in which altered cation specificity is observed or in which sugar transport is uncoupled from cation symport (i.e.%2C uniport is catalyzed). The various members of the family can use Na+%2C H+ or Li%2C Na+ or Li+%2C H+ or Li+%2C or only H+ as the symported cation. All of these proteins possess twelve putative transmembrane a-helical spanners. [Transport and binding proteins%2C Carbohydrates%2C organic alcohols%2C and acids] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-260%2C Eval:7.0e-07%2C score:48.4%2C N-term missing],MGA_391
