NODE_24_length_29178_cov_418.042748	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	20039	22003	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1521;product=biotin carboxylase N-terminal domain-containing protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_007053766.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_15000;note=WP_007053766.1 biotin carboxylase N-terminal domain-containing protein (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:94.2%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:0.0e+00],Domain:cl27361:Biotin_carb_C Biotin carboxylase C-terminal domain. Members of this family are ATP-dependent urea carboxylase%2C including characterized members from Oleomonas sagaranensis (alpha class Proteobacterium) and yeasts such as Saccharomyces cerevisiae. The allophanate hydrolase domain of the yeast enzyme is not included in this model and is represented by an adjacent gene in Oleomonas sagaranensis. The fusion of urea carboxylase and allophanate hydrolase is designated urea amidolyase. The enzyme from Oleomonas sagaranensis was shown to be highly active on acetamide and formamide as well as urea. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Nitrogen metabolism] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:6-611%2C Eval:0.0e+00%2C score:576.6],MGA_1521
